  "commentary": "With SPX at 6572.27 trading below the 6599 flip in a PIN regime, dealers are long gamma and will mechanically sell any push toward the massive 6600 resistance wall (16.4B GEX) while providing buying support above the 6550 negative gamma zone (-12.1B GEX). The regime flip and GEX surge suggest we just transitioned from a more volatile environment into this stabilizing setup, with dealers now positioned to fade directional moves and compress realized volatility. Key levels: defend 6550 downside amplification zone, expect heavy selling pressure into 6580-6600 resistance cluster.\n\nBottom line: expect the market to get pinned between 6550-6600 with limited breakout potential.",
